## Why This License Structure

This research has dual-use implications documented in ethics.md. The
share-alike requirement on documents ensures that anyone who builds on
this spec — including the ontology design, geometric monitoring methods,
and vocabulary architecture — must share their additions openly. The AGPL
on code ensures that deployments of geometric monitoring tools based on
this work cannot be made proprietary, including when deployed as a
network service.

These licenses do not prevent misuse. They create legal standing for the
community to require openness from anyone who builds on this work. The
ethical constraints in ethics.md are the moral framework; these licenses
are the legal one.

